Tasks: 40\n506\t- Correct: 26 / 40 (65.0%)\n507\t- Rules: 32 -> 33 (+1 learned)\n508\t- Stored rule hits: 25\n509\t- Time: 19s\n510\t- Log: logs/learn_20260429_093322.log\n511\t\n512\t---\n513\t## Session 12 -- 2026-04-29\n514\t\n515\t**Strategy added:** `mirror_shoot_anchor`\n516\t\n517\tA full-row or full-column divider line of color D splits the grid into\n518\ttwo regions. The 'object' region contains connected components made\n519\tfrom two foreground colors: anchor A and pointer P. The 'marker' region\n520\tcontains scattered cells of a third color M, each placed at the mirror\n521\t(across the divider) of an A cell. Output: each anchor moves to the\n522\tfarthest connected pointer cell along its trail (BFS through P cells);\n523\teach marker moves to the mirror of the new anchor; original A, P and\n524\tM cells become background.\n525\t\n526\t- Solves: c9680e90 (and category of mirror+pointer-trail tasks)\n527\t- Anchor color discovered by checking which color's cell positions\n528\t  mirror-match the marker positions across the divider.\n529\t- Both row and column dividers are supported.\n530\t- Placed BEFORE `recolor_sequential` (which would false-positive on\n531\t  these tasks since a 2 -> 6 recolor looks like a sequential recolor\n532\t  to the cell-level diff analysis).\n533\t\n534\t**Result:** 25/40 -> 26/40 (62.5% -> 65.0%), +1 rule learned (rule_033)\n535\t- c9680e90: CORRECT via mirror_shoot_anchor (newly discovered)\n536\t\n537\tVerification:\n538\t- `python run_task.py` (regression on 08ed6ac7): CORRECT\n539\t- `python run_learn.py --limit 40 --shuffle`: 26 / 40 (65.0%)\n540\t- Rules: 32 -> 33\n541\t\n542\t---\n543\t## Learning Loop -- 2026-04-29 09:34\n544\t\n545\t- Split: None, Tasks: 40\n546\t- Correct: 26 / 40 (65.0%)\n547\t- Rules: 33 -> 33 (+0 learned)\n548\t- Stored rule hits: 26\n549\t- Time: 19s\n550\t- Log: logs/learn_20260429_093417.log\n551\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"146f1467-824d-4bf5-85ef-b2da610f2a6f","uuid":"2442